<h4 style="font-size: 25px; line-height: 32px;">Recorded Lands and Taxation</h4>
<h6 style="font-size: 16px; margin-top: 40px;">The Office of Tax and Revenue (OTR) maintains a database known as the Integrated Tax System (ITS) containing the accounts for real estate property. ITS records property transactions, such as reconfigured lots & ownership change, as they occur during a given fiscal year. DC government's fiscal year begin October 1st and ends September 30th.  Below are the six different lot types in the District. Individually, these key layers make up most of the District's property boundaries. Together, they make up a single layer known as the common ownership lots and dimensions.</h6>
